**Module Examples:**

```
Object contains multiple UpdateModule instances:
├── PhysicsUpdate        → Movement, collision
├── AIUpdate            → Combat AI, pathfinding
├── WeaponUpdate        → Firing, cooldowns
├── DamageModule        → Health/armor
├── ProductionUpdate    → Building production (for factories)
├── LocomotorUpdate     → Walking/flying animation
└── ... ~100+ module types
```

**Update Schedule:**

```cpp
// File: Code/GameEngine/Include/GameLogic/Module/UpdateModule.h

enum SleepyUpdatePhase {
    PHASE_INITIAL = 0,     // Resolve object creation/deletion
    PHASE_PHYSICS = 1,     // Physics updates (movement)
    PHASE_NORMAL = 2,      // Standard updates (combat, AI)
    PHASE_FINAL = 3,       // Cleanup and rendering updates
};

// Within GameLogic each frame:
for (frame 0 to N_frames) {
    // Phase 0: Create/delete objects
    for (each object) { if (object->isAwake()) update(PHASE_INITIAL); }

    // Phase 1: Physics
    for (each object) { if (object->isAwake()) update(PHASE_PHYSICS); }

    // Phase 2: Standard logic
    for (each object) { if (object->isAwake()) update(PHASE_NORMAL); }

    // Phase 3: Final (visual updates)
    for (each object) { if (object->isAwake()) update(PHASE_FINAL); }
}
```

