BehaviorModule                  [Include/GameLogic/Module/BehaviorModule.h]
├─ UpdateModule                 [Include/GameLogic/Module/UpdateModule.h]
│  ├─ PhysicsUpdate
│  ├─ AIUpdate
│  ├─ WeaponUpdate
│  ├─ ProductionUpdate
│  └─ ... ~100 types

// Player structure
Player {
    Money m_money;
    Int m_powerPoints;
    std::list<Object*> m_allObjects;
    Science m_sciences[];
    UpgradeTemplate m_upgrades[];
};

// Message system
GameMessage {
    Type m_type;
    GameMessageArgument *m_argList;
};
```

---

## 8. CRITICAL FILES FOR HEADLESS ENGINE

### Must Include (Core Logic)

```
GameEngine/
├── Include/Common/GameCommon.h        *** Frame rate: LOGICFRAMES_PER_SECOND = 30
├── Include/Common/GameEngine.h        *** Main engine interface
├── Include/GameLogic/GameLogic.h      *** Game state manager
├── Include/GameLogic/Object.h         *** Entity class
├── Include/Common/Player.h            *** Player state
├── Include/GameLogic/PartitionManager.h *** Fog of war
├── Include/GameLogic/AI.h             *** AI system
├── Include/Common/MessageStream.h     *** Command system
├── Include/GameNetwork/NetCommandMsg.h *** Network commands
├── Include/GameLogic/Module/UpdateModule.h *** Behavior modules
├── Source/Common/GameEngine.cpp       *** Main loop
├── Source/GameLogic/GameLogic.cpp     *** Game state updates
└── Source/GameEngine/Source/GameLogic/Object/Object.cpp *** Entity logic
```

### Must Stub (Rendering/Audio)

```
GameEngineDevice/
├── W3DDevice/                  *** ENTIRE RENDERING LAYER
├── MilesAudioDevice/           *** ENTIRE AUDIO LAYER
├── VideoDevice/                *** ENTIRE VIDEO/CUTSCENE LAYER
└── Win32Device/                *** ENTIRE WINDOWS LAYER
```

### Entry Point

```
Main/WinMain.cpp               *** Modify to create headless engine
```

---

## 9. BUILD CONFIGURATION

### Project Files

**Both Generals and GeneralsMD use:**
- `Code/RTS.dsp` - Visual Studio 6.0 project (master solution)
- `Code/RTS.dsw` - Visual Studio 6.0 workspace (master)
- Individual `.dsp` files:
  - `GameEngine/GameEngine.dsp` - Core library
  - `GameEngineDevice/GameEngineDevice.dsp` - Rendering library
  - Multiple tool projects

### Dependencies (from README.md)

```
Required external libraries:
- DirectX SDK (9.0+)           → Code/Libraries/DirectX/
- STLport (4.5.3)              → Code/Libraries/STLport-4.5.3
- 3DSMax 4 SDK                 → Code/Libraries/Max4SDK/
- Miles Sound System            → Code/Libraries/Source/WWVegas/Miles6/
- Bink Video SDK               → Code/GameEngineDevice/Include/VideoDevice/Bink
- GameSpy SDK                  → Code/Libraries/Source/GameSpy/
- ZLib (1.1.4)                 → Code/Libraries/Source/Compression/ZLib/
```

### Headless Build Strategy

1. Remove DirectX, Miles, Bink, GameSpy dependencies
2. Create `GameEngineHeadless.dsp` - Excludes all GameEngineDevice
3. Link only GameEngine + Libraries/Source
4. Replace WinMain with custom headless entry point
5. Use existing GameLogic/AI unchanged

---

## 10. DATA FLOW FOR AI INTEGRATION

### State Extraction Example

```cpp
// Get all units for player 0
GameLogic *logic = TheGameLogic;
Player *player = logic->getPlayer(0);

// Iterate units
for (Object *unit = player->getFirstObject(); unit; unit = unit->getNextObject()) {
    // Read unit state
    ObjectID id = unit->getId();
    Coord3D pos = unit->getPosition();
    Int health = unit->getHealth();
    ThingTemplate *tmpl = unit->getTemplate();
    AsciiString name = tmpl->getName();

    // Check visibility from player 1's perspective
    ObjectShroudStatus shroud = unit->getShroudStatus(1);
    if (shroud == OBJECTSHROUD_CLEAR) {
        // Player 1 can see this unit
    }
}

// Get resources
UnsignedInt money = player->getMoney()->countMoney();
Int power = player->getPowerPoints();
```

### Action Injection Example

```cpp
// Move unit to location
Object *unit = logic->findObjectByID(unitID);
unit->setPosition(Coord3D(100, 50, 0));

// Attack target
Object *target = logic->findObjectByID(targetID);
unit->setAttackTarget(target);

// Give attack move command (implicit attack while moving)
unit->setFormationAttackMoving(true);

// Build structure
Object *builder = logic->findObjectByID(builderID);
// Note: Building production handled by ProductionUpdate module
// Must use proper command system for most complex actions
```

---

## 11. SNAPSHOT & SERIALIZATION SYSTEM

**All game objects inherit from `Snapshot`:**

```cpp
// File: Include/Common/Snapshot.h

class Snapshot {
    virtual void crc(Xfer *xfer);      // Calculate checksum (for multiplayer sync)
    virtual void xfer(Xfer *xfer);     // Serialize state (for save/load)
    virtual void loadPostProcess();    // Post-load initialization
};
```

**Used for:**
- Save/load game functionality
- Replay recording
- **Multiplayer CRC checks** (verify all players have same game state)

**For headless engine:**
- Can replay recorded games
- Can snapshot state for AI training datasets
- Can verify multiplayer consistency

---

## 12. CRITICAL DESIGN PATTERNS

### 1. Singleton Pattern

```cpp
GameEngine *TheGameEngine;           // Global instance
GameLogic *TheGameLogic;
GameClient *TheGameClient;
MessageStream *TheMessageStream;
Display *TheDisplay;                 // Can be W3DDisplay or NullDisplay
```

### 2. Factory Pattern

```cpp
// ThingFactory creates objects from templates
class ThingFactory {
    Object *createObject(ThingTemplate *tmpl, ObjectStatusBits status, Team *team);
};

ModuleFactory *TheModuleFactory;     // Creates behavior modules
```

### 3. Observer Pattern

```cpp
// MessageStream routes messages to subscribers
class MessageStream {
    TranslatorID registerTranslator(Translator *t);  // Subscribe to messages
    void sendMessage(GameMessage *msg);              // Broadcast
};
```

### 4. Component Pattern

```cpp
// Objects contain multiple UpdateModule components
Object {
    UpdateModule *m_updateModules[MAX_UPDATE_MODULES];
    // Each module handles one aspect of behavior
};
```

---

## CONCLUSION

The C&C Generals Zero Hour source code is **well-architected for headless operation**:

1. **Clear separation:** GameLogic (logic-only) vs GameEngineDevice (rendering-only)
2. **Virtual interfaces:** Display, AudioManager, etc. are abstract (stub-friendly)
3. **Fixed tick rate:** 30 FPS deterministic, no rendering dependency
4. **Modular objects:** UpdateModule system is flexible and easy to extend
5. **Complete state:** Everything needed for AI training is in GameLogic

**Implementation Plan:**
1. Build GameEngine.lib without GameEngineDevice
2. Implement NullDisplay stub
3. Create custom WinMain → direct API calls
4. Inject AI decisions via Object::setPosition(), ::setAttackTarget(), etc.
5. Read game state from GameLogic singletons
6. Loop at 30 Hz fixed rate

The codebase is C++/DirectX 9, requiring modernization but the architecture is sound for headless operation.

