# ZH Engine Architecture — Source Code Analysis

> **Date:** 2026-04-01
> **Source:** `cczh-source-code/` (EA open-source, GPL v3)
> **Purpose:** Reference for headless engine build and AI integration (Plan 1)

---

## 1. Repository Structure

```
cczh-source-code/
├── Generals/               # Original C&C Generals (v1.0)
│   └── Code/
│       ├── GameEngine/         # Core game logic (platform-agnostic)
│       ├── GameEngineDevice/   # Rendering/audio (platform-specific)
│       ├── Main/               # Windows entry point (WinMain.cpp)
│       ├── Libraries/          # Third-party dependencies
│       └── Tools/              # Development tools
│
└── GeneralsMD/             # Zero Hour expansion (identical code structure)
    └── Code/               # Same layout as Generals/
```

**Generals vs GeneralsMD:** GeneralsMD is Zero Hour. Code architecture is identical — differences are in INI data (units, maps, balance). Use GeneralsMD for training.

---

## 2. GameEngine Module Structure

```
Code/GameEngine/
├── Include/
│   ├── Common/          # Shared headers: GameEngine, Player, Money, MessageStream
│   ├── GameClient/      # UI, camera, input headers
│   ├── GameLogic/       # Object, AI, PartitionManager headers
│   └── GameNetwork/     # NetCommandMsg headers
│
└── Source/
    ├── Common/          # GameEngine.cpp, Player.cpp
    ├── GameClient/      # UI, input, drawable
    ├── GameLogic/       # Object.cpp, GameLogic.cpp, AI/
    └── GameNetwork/     # Multiplayer commands
```

---

## 3. Key Constants

```cpp
// Code/GameEngine/Include/Common/GameCommon.h (Line 66)
enum {
    LOGICFRAMES_PER_SECOND = 30,   // Fixed 30 Hz tick rate
    MSEC_PER_SECOND = 1000
};
// Decision rate for AI: every 10 ticks = 3 decisions/sec = 333ms
```

---

## 4. Main Game Loop

```
WinMain()  [Code/Main/WinMain.cpp]
    → Win32GameEngine::init()
        → GameLogic::init()      — object factory, AI, map load, players
        → GameClient::init()     — display, keyboard, mouse
        → MessageStream::init()
    → Win32GameEngine::execute()  [MAIN LOOP]
        while !quitting:
            serviceWindowsOS()   — Windows messages
            GameEngine::update()
                GameLogic::update()   — *** CORE SIMULATION ***
                    processCommandList()
                    for each frame phase (0-3):
                        UpdateModule::update() on each object
                    check victory conditions
                GameClient::update()  — camera, input, UI
                MessageStream::update()
            Display::draw()       — render (stub this out)
```

**For headless:** Call `GameLogic::update()` at 30 Hz. Stub `Display` and `GameClient`.

---

## 5. Entity System (Object)

```cpp
// Code/GameEngine/Include/GameLogic/Object.h

class Object : public Thing, public Snapshot {
    ObjectID        m_id;           // Unique entity ID
    ThingTemplate  *m_template;     // INI template (unit type, stats)
    Player         *m_owner;        // Owner player
    Team           *m_team;
    Coord3D         m_position;     // World position (x, y, z)
    Real            m_angle;        // Facing angle
    Int             m_health;       // Current HP
    VeterancyLevel  m_veterancy;    // REGULAR, VETERAN, ELITE, HEROIC
    ObjectStatusBits m_status;      // State flags (moving, attacking, dead...)
    UpdateModule   *m_updateModules[]; // Behavior modules
    Drawable       *m_drawable;     // Visual (null in headless)
    ObjectShroudStatus m_shroudStatus; // Fog of war status
};

enum ObjectShroudStatus {
    OBJECTSHROUD_CLEAR,
    OBJECTSHROUD_PARTIAL_CLEAR,
    OBJECTSHROUD_FOGGED,    // Seen before, not now
    OBJECTSHROUD_SHROUDED   // Never seen
};
```

**Behavior is modular** — each unit has a list of `UpdateModule` components (physics, AI, weapons, production, etc). No hardcoded behavior per unit type.

---

## 6. Player State

```cpp
// Code/GameEngine/Include/Common/Player.h

class Player : public Snapshot {
    PlayerIndex  m_playerIndex;       // 0-15 (MAX_PLAYER_COUNT = 16)
    AsciiString  m_side;              // "USA", "China", "GLA"
    Money        m_money;             // UnsignedInt m_money
    Int          m_powerPoints;       // Power surplus/deficit
    std::list<Object*> m_allObjects;  // All owned units/buildings
    Science      m_sciences[];        // Researched tech
    UpgradeTemplate *m_upgrades[];    // Applied upgrades
    SpecialPowerReadyTimer m_specialPowers[]; // Cooldowns
};
```

---

## 7. Command / Action Injection

**Command flow:**
```
AI Decision
    → GameMessage (type + args)
    → CommandList queue
    → GameLogic::processCommandList()
    → Object::issueCommand()
    → UpdateModule executes
```

```cpp
// Code/GameEngine/Include/Common/MessageStream.h
class GameMessage {
    enum Type { MSG_MOVE_UNIT, MSG_ATTACK_TARGET, MSG_BUILD_STRUCTURE, ... };
    // ~200+ message types
    GameMessageArgument *m_argList;  // objectID, location, etc.
};

// Code/GameEngine/Include/GameNetwork/NetCommandMsg.h
class NetCommandMsg {
    UnsignedInt m_executionFrame;  // Deterministic execution frame
    UnsignedInt m_playerID;
    NetCommandType m_commandType;
    GameMessage *constructGameMessage();
};
```

**Direct manipulation (for headless training):**
```cpp
unit->setPosition(Coord3D(x, y, z));
unit->setAttackTarget(targetObject);
unit->setFormationAttackMoving(true);
UnsignedInt money = player->getMoney()->countMoney();
Int power = player->getPowerPoints();
```

---

## 8. Fog of War

```cpp
// Code/GameEngine/Include/GameLogic/PartitionManager.h

class PartitionManager {
    PartitionCell m_cells[GRID_WIDTH][GRID_HEIGHT];
    // Per-cell shroud status per player
    // Updated each frame based on unit sight radii
};

// Query:
ObjectShroudStatus shroud = unit->getShroudStatus(playerIndex);
// OBJECTSHROUD_CLEAR = visible to that player right now
```

---

## 9. Rendering Layer (GameEngineDevice) — Stub This Out

```
Code/GameEngineDevice/
├── W3DDevice/        # DirectX 9 rendering (Westwood 3D engine)
├── MilesAudioDevice/ # Miles Sound System
├── VideoDevice/      # Bink video codec (cutscenes)
└── Win32Device/      # Windows OS (HWND, WndProc)
```

**Rendering uses a virtual interface:**
```cpp
// Code/GameEngine/Include/GameClient/Display.h
class Display : public SubsystemInterface {
    virtual void draw() = 0;
    virtual void drawLine(...) = 0;
    // ~20 pure virtual methods
};
// W3DDisplay implements this — replace with NullDisplay
```

**Stub strategy:**
```cpp
class NullDisplay : public Display {
    void draw() override {}       // no-op all methods
    void drawLine(...) override {}
    // ...
};
```

---

## 10. Singleton Architecture

```cpp
// Global singletons (accessed everywhere)
GameEngine    *TheGameEngine;
GameLogic     *TheGameLogic;
GameClient    *TheGameClient;
MessageStream *TheMessageStream;
Display       *TheDisplay;        // Swap for NullDisplay
ThingFactory  *TheThingFactory;
ModuleFactory *TheModuleFactory;
```

---

## 11. Serialization / Snapshot

All game objects inherit `Snapshot`:
```cpp
class Snapshot {
    virtual void xfer(Xfer *xfer);         // Serialize full state
    virtual void crc(Xfer *xfer);          // Checksum for MP sync
    virtual void loadPostProcess();
};
```

Used for save/load AND multiplayer CRC verification. Can snapshot game state at any tick for dataset generation.

---

## 12. State Extraction Pattern (for pybind11)

```cpp
// Iterate all objects for a player
Player *player = TheGameLogic->getPlayer(playerIndex);
for (Object *obj = player->getFirstObject(); obj; obj = obj->getNextObject()) {
    ObjectID   id     = obj->getId();
    Coord3D    pos    = obj->getPosition();
    Int        hp     = obj->getHealth();
    AsciiString type  = obj->getTemplate()->getName();
    ObjectShroudStatus vis = obj->getShroudStatus(observerPlayerIndex);
}

// Fog of war grid
PartitionManager *pm = ThePartitionManager;
// Query cell shroud by world coordinate
```

---

## 13. Build Dependencies (to strip for headless)

| Keep | Strip |
|------|-------|
| `GameEngine/` (all) | `GameEngineDevice/W3DDevice/` |
| `Libraries/Source/` | `GameEngineDevice/MilesAudioDevice/` |
| `GameLogic/` | `GameEngineDevice/VideoDevice/` |
| `GameNetwork/` (commands only) | `GameEngineDevice/Win32Device/` |
| | `DirectX SDK` |
| | `Miles SDK` |
| | `Bink SDK` |
| | `GameSpy SDK` |

---

## 14. Headless Engine Build Plan

1. Create `CMakeLists.txt` targeting `GameEngine/` sources only
2. Implement `NullDisplay : public Display` (all no-ops)
3. Implement `NullAudioDevice` (all no-ops)
4. Replace `WinMain` with a headless `main()` entry point
5. Initialize `TheGameLogic` directly — skip `Win32GameEngine`
6. Run loop: `TheGameLogic->update()` at 30 Hz
7. Expose state/actions via pybind11 → Python gym environment

**Key risk:** Win32 API calls scattered throughout codebase. May need stub headers for `HWND`, `HINSTANCE` etc. on non-Windows builds (or build under Wine/Windows VM initially).

